00:08:44.080 --> 00:08:49.320
Yeah, I'd imagine as time goes on, they're really cooking on it and figuring it out.

00:08:49.320 --> 00:08:56.039
Maybe you could psychoanalyze it as that fixation on efficiency and thinking about how to do

00:08:56.039 --> 00:09:06.039
things optimally. Translate it in some way to building tools. And later on, it frustrates

00:09:06.039 --> 00:09:12.200
me that doing this task related to data processing or related to data science is tedious or inefficient.

00:09:12.200 --> 00:09:17.320
And so I want to find a way to make it fit my brain better or make it more efficient.

00:09:17.320 --> 00:09:23.599
And so in a sense, I guess it's just a personality trait of trying to speed run the data science

00:09:23.599 --> 00:09:25.080
workflow a little bit.

00:09:25.119 --> 00:09:31.719
Yeah, that's fair. And I guess you see that with Pandas too, some of the optimizing and

00:09:31.719 --> 00:09:35.200
speeding up that there's a lot. I feel like through your work, there's a lot of kind of

00:09:35.200 --> 00:09:38.200
optimizing and speeding up.

00:09:38.200 --> 00:09:46.280
Yeah, early on in Pandas, because it was the only tool around for a lot of the things that

00:09:46.280 --> 00:09:52.640
